@gsalgado I'd like to get your thoughts on this. My current general thoughts on how to approach this are:

Setup two `reader,writer` pairs, `r1,w1` and `r2,w2` such that `w2` is the main writer and `r1` is the main reader.  Data flows `w2 -> r2 -> w1 -> r1`.  Then we create a long running asynchronous loop which continually reads from `r2` and writes what it reads to `w1`.

You can think of this as buffering the data from the main writer to the main reader via an intermediate step (which sort of unintentionally simulates the actual networking).

